dcterms:description: A synthetic dataset generated to model heterogeneous treatment effects, where the outcome is influenced by a set of features and treatment assignment is deterministic based on specific functions.

dcterms:description: A semi-synthetic dataset derived from the Infant Health and Development Program (IHDP), containing real features and treatment assignments but simulated responses to evaluate causal inference methods.
